fullName.value: T-complex protein 1 subunit eta, N-terminally processed

texts.value: Component of the chaperonin-containing T-complex (TRiC), a molecular chaperone complex that assists the folding of proteins upon ATP hydrolysis (PubMed:25467444). The TRiC complex mediates the folding of WRAP53/TCAB1, thereby regulating telomere maintenance (PubMed:25467444). The TRiC complex plays a role in the folding of actin and tubulin (Probable)

Component of the chaperonin-containing T-complex (TRiC), a heterooligomeric complex of about 850 to 900 kDa that forms two stacked rings, 12 to 16 nm in diameter (PubMed:25467444). Interacts with PACRG (PubMed:14532270). Interacts with DLEC1 (PubMed:33144677)
Belongs to the TCP-1 chaperonin family
